      "message": "[Critical] Line 43: The JSON-controlled `file` field is joined directly with `REPO_ROOT`, so an absolute path or `../` path in a crafted import file can cause the script to overwrite arbitrary files when run by a maintainer. Restrict imports to the expected `translations/jami_client_qt_\u003clang\u003e.ts` files and reject paths that resolve outside the translations directory. For example:\n```suggestion\n    rel_file \u003d payload[\u0027file\u0027]\n    ts_path \u003d os.path.realpath(os.path.join(REPO_ROOT, rel_file))\n    translations_dir \u003d os.path.realpath(os.path.join(REPO_ROOT, \u0027translations\u0027))\n    if not ts_path.startswith(translations_dir + os.sep):\n        raise ValueError(\u0027invalid translation target: {}\u0027.format(rel_file))\n```",
