      "message": "[Major] Line 94: `_xml_escape()` escapes quotes and apostrophes in element text, which turns normal translator input like `Don\u0026apos;t` from exported JSON into `Don\u0026amp;apos;t` in the `.ts` file if a translator preserves existing XML entities. Because the export uses parsed text, the import should either document that translators must use raw characters only and reject entity-looking input, or unescape before escaping. A safer fix is to normalize with `html.unescape()` before XML escaping:\n```suggestion\nimport html\n...\ndef _xml_escape(text):\n    text \u003d html.unescape(text)\n    return (text.replace(\u0027\u0026\u0027, \u0027\u0026amp;\u0027)\n                .replace(\u0027\u003c\u0027, \u0027\u0026lt;\u0027)\n                .replace(\u0027\u003e\u0027, \u0027\u0026gt;\u0027))\n```",
